originalText.text:
Joy's substitutions for healthier choices are a blessing . I think I have tried everything but I will not have surgery.
The food ideas are simple and easy to follow.
The only problem I'm having is finding a whole grain bread with a total slice of no more than 50 calories each slice. No bagel ,no slice of bread comes close  except English muffin.
Perhaps someone could make a recommendation?
Aso, if a recipe calls for sugar, is their something else I could use being a diabetic I don't use honey maple syrup or sugar.   What's a
good substitution?
I would so appreciate a suggestion.  I have exhausted all avenues on my end.
thank you
D.ortizio
